ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR DATASET AND PROCESSED RESULTS
(Supplementary to the MIT License above)

The processed results included in this repository — including automatically
generated lesion masks, PNG visualizations, and quality metric tables — are
provided for scientific, educational, and research purposes only.

1. COMMERCIAL USE: Commercial use of the processed results requires prior
   written agreement with the project authors.

2. ATTRIBUTION: Any scientific publication, thesis, or research work making
   use of this dataset or its results must cite both this project and the
   original Aphasia Recovery Cohort dataset (OpenNeuro ds004884).

3. RE-IDENTIFICATION: Attempting to re-identify research participants from
   the anonymized data is strictly prohibited. Source data has been
   de-identified in accordance with Safe Harbor guidelines, including
   application of the spm_deface algorithm.

4. ETHICAL USE: Users agree to use the data in compliance with applicable
   research ethics standards, including the principles of the World Medical
   Association Declaration of Helsinki.

5. CLINICAL USE: The automatic segmentation results are not validated for
   clinical use. Any clinical application requires prior verification by a
   qualified neuroradiologist.

6. MODIFICATIONS TO TERMS: The project authors reserve the right to amend
   these additional terms for future versions of the dataset. Amendments
   apply to subsequently released versions only.
